Section 7. Security considerations:
ez:// uses a constrained character set: a-z, A-Z, 0-9, dot, slash, question mark, hash. The scheme uses fixed 3-level parsing without DNS recursion. URI length is constrained to 128 bytes. Implementations must validate character set and length before parsing.

